                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.991H/8–1049: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Kunming</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lutkins</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Kunming</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-08-10T09:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 10, 1949—9 a. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 12—3:56 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>122. ReDeptel 56, August 3, 7 p. m. Permission requested to inform in confidence
                    heads various mission groups of closure decision to give them adequate time for
                    making plans.</p>
                <p>CAT pilot tells me that closure common knowledge in Canton and Hong Kong. Though
                    I fear damage has been done, I am trying to plug leak with CAT here. Request
                    Canton do same.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 122, repeated Office of the Embassy, Canton 38.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lutkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
